Isa Ali Pantami, the Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, has lost his 13-year-old daughter, Aishah Isa Ali. The Minister announced the sad story via his official Twitter account @DrIsaPantami on Monday. He said that the funeral prayer for his daughter will be conducted in Abuja (today) Tuesday at Annur Masjeed, Wuse 2. He tweeted, “Inna lil Laahi wa inna ilaiHi Rajiun! My 13-year old daughter, Aishah Isa Ali (Amal) passed away just a moment ago. “Due to some necessities, funeral prayer (today )at Annur Masjeed, Wuse 2, immediately after Zuhr prayer in sha Allah. May Allah forgive & be Merciful to her.” Isa Ali Ibrahim also known as Sheikh Pantami was the immediate past Director General of NITDA and was nominated as minister and sworn into office on the 21st of August, 2019.